      <description>&lt;p&gt;Craig is a PhD Student of Literacy Education &amp;amp; Human Development and Family Studies at Iowa State University. He works under the mentorship of &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.education.iastate.edu/directory/profile.php?u=cbeecher&amp;embedded=true&#34;&gt;Dr. Connie Beecher&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.hdfs.hs.iastate.edu/directory/profile.php?u=jychoi&amp;embedded=true&#34;&gt;Dr. Ji Young Choi&lt;/a&gt; investigating the language and literacy development of young children in the home and preschool contexts. Craig has worked on several evaluations, investigating parent-education programs, Iowa&amp;rsquo;s Statewide Voluntary Preschool Program, and the implementation of Iowa Project LAUNCH in Head Start. He is currently working on examining early language intervention effects on children&amp;rsquo;s language outcomes, preschool language environments for Dual Language Learners, and preschool teachers&amp;rsquo; beliefs on teaching practices.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
